		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>Nonparametric Bayesian methods are developed for analysis of multi-channel spike-train data, with the feature learning and spike sorting performed jointly. The feature learning and sorting are performed simultaneously across all channels. Dictionary learning is implemented via the beta-Bernoulli process, with spike sorting performed via the dynamic hierarchical Dirichlet process (dHDP), with these two models coupled. The dHDP is augmented to eliminate refractory-period violations, it allows the &quot;appearance&quot; and &quot;disappearance&quot; of neurons over time, and it models smooth variation in the spike statistics.</p>
			</abstract>
